<category>
	<pattern>WHY DO YOU THINK THE BANK RECEPTIONIST IS SO IMPORTANT</pattern>
	<template>
		<random>
			<li>I believe that a bank receptionist embodies the "look" and "feel" of personal service today's bank seek to convey to clients.</li>
			<li>A receptionist is the first face a client sees when entering the bank.</li>
			<li>The receptionist is the first point of contact for a consumer who calls the financial institution.</li>
			<li>A bank receptionist has the power to start of a client's banking experience on a positive note.</li>
			<li>A rude bank receptionist may put a client on edge and also place them on the defensive.</li>
			<li>If the bank receptionist is poorly trained or selected for the position, the bank could suffer by losing clients.</li>
		</random></template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>WHAT IS THE BASIC JOB DECRIPTION FOR THE BANK RECEPTIONIST</pattern>
	<template>The basic job description for the bank receptionist is they act as liaison between clients and bank personnel. They perform basic clerical duties and display a professional impression for all that enter the bank. The job description is a mix of administrative work, basic banking tasks, and a high degree of customer service.</template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>CAN THE BANK RECEPTIONIST HAVE AN EXPANDED JOB DESCRIPTION</pattern>
	<template>Yes, it could include supply management and file maintenance. Some cases assist clients when accessing their safe deposit box. If a receptionist is bilingual, they may frequently assist foreign clients and translate interactions between bank personnel and the consumer. The smaller the bank the more extensive the expanded bank receptionist's job description becomes. The receptionist could double as an administrative assistant to a bank manager or sales manager.</template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>WHAT TYPE OF ATTITUDE DOES THE BANK RECEPTIONIST NEED TO HAVE</pattern>
	<template>
		<random>
			<li>A personality that is unshakeable.</li>
			<li>Must be energetic from the moment the bank opens until the time it closes.</li>
			<li>Strive for a nonstop professional attitude and outward appearance.</li>
			<li>Receive constructive criticism from bank personnel without problems.</li>
		</random></template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>DOES THE BANK RECEPTIONIST NEED TO BE COMPUTER LITERATE</pattern>
	<template>Yes, a successful bank receptionist must be computer literate in Microsoft Word and Excel.</template>
</category>
