			<li>To be able to type a minimum of 50 words a minutes.</li>
			<li>Understand the need for client confidentiality.</li>
			<li>Working at the front desk requires a lot of multi-tasking.</li>
			<li>Keep the area clean and appealing to clients.</li>
			<li>Have a clean, uncluttered, and organized desk.</li>
			<li>Outside training in areas within the job description.</li>
			<li>Act as liaison between clients and bank personnel.</li>
			<li>Perform basic clerical duties.</li>
			<li>Have a professional impression on the general public.</li>
		</random></template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>WHY DOES A BANK HAVE A RECEPTIONIST</pattern>
	<template>
		<random>
			<li>To answer questions for clients.</li>
			<li>Answer general questions regarding services offered by the bank.</li>
			<li>Customer service.</li>
		</random></template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>DO YOU NEED PREVIOUS BANKING EXPERIENCE</pattern>
	<template>Not necessary at a bank, but previous experience in an organization performing duties comparable to those of a telephone switchboard operator and general clerk experience.</template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>DO YOU NEED SPECIAL SKILLS</pattern>
	<template>It helps.</template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>WHAT TYPE OF SPECIAL SKILLS</pattern>
	<template>Possess a pleasant telephone voice and the ability to perate a telephone switchboard. Ability to learn staff names and functions in a reasonable amount of time. Customer service orientation and the ability to maintain confidentiality. Good interpersonal, communication, and good computer skills.</template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>CAN YOU SUMMARIZE YOUR POSITION</pattern>
	<template>Operate a multi-line telephone system, give routine information to the clients, greet each and every person that enters the bank, performs routine clerical work such as typing, filing, scheduling, and accept special deliveries.</template>
</category>
<category>
	<pattern>ESSENTIAL DUTIES FOR THE POSITION INCLUDE</pattern>
	<template>
		<random>
			<li>Receive calls and give information to callers.</li>
			<li>Screen and route calls to appropriate destination.</li>
			<li>Greet visitors, staff, and others in a professional and courteous manner.</li>
			<li>Participate in the recruiting process by receiving and screening resumes, scheduling of interviews and communicating with public on job openings and application process.</li>
			<li>Assist with the setup of phones and employee extensions.</li>
			<li>Check the banks general email box.</li>
			<li>Perform routine clerical work, as time permits.</li>
			<li>Order and maintain Human Resources Departmental supplies.</li>
			<li>Perform other job duties or special projects as required.</li>
		</random></template>
</category>
